{
  "doc_id": "30568",
  "text": "Nested governance in the commercial fishery is moderately present [CITATION_1] , CGRCS 2010 , IPHC 2014 . A moderate level of collaborative management is achieved through organizations like the CIC, IPHC, and CGRCS. These organizations assist in the management of the commercial fishery through stock assessments, annual meetings, and yearly regulatory suggestions [CITATION_2] , CGRCS 2010 , IPHC 2014 . However, these independent organizations act only as advisory bodies, with the official decision-making power resting at the federal level [CITATION_3] . Nevertheless, the involvement of the commercial sector in the decision-making process is extensive and constitutes a significant level of informal nested governance.",
